# Spring Boot Controller Patterns

## 📌 PURPOSE

Controllers handle HTTP requests and return responses.

---

## 🚨 CONTRACT-FIRST (MANDATORY)

### DO

* Implement endpoints defined in OpenAPI:

  * `design-inputs/api-contracts/task-tracker.yaml`
* Match request/response exactly

### DO NOT

* Do not create endpoints without contract

---

## 🧱 STRUCTURE

### DO

* Use `@RestController`
* Use `@RequestMapping("/v1/tasks")`

### EXAMPLE

```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/v1/tasks")
public class TaskController {

    private final TaskService taskService;

    public TaskController(TaskService taskService) {
        this.taskService = taskService;
    }
}
```

---

## 🔁 ENDPOINT PATTERNS

```java
GET    /tasks
GET    /tasks/{id}
POST   /tasks
PUT    /tasks/{id}
PATCH  /tasks/{id}
DELETE /tasks/{id}
```

---

## 📥 REQUEST HANDLING

### DO

* Use DTOs with `@RequestBody`
* Use `@PathVariable`
* Use `@RequestParam`

### EXAMPLE

```java
@PostMapping
public ResponseEntity<TaskResponse> create(
        @Valid @RequestBody CreateTaskRequest request) {
    return ResponseEntity.status(201)
        .body(taskService.create(request));
}
```

---

## 📤 RESPONSE HANDLING

### DO

* Return `ResponseEntity`
* Use correct HTTP status codes

### DO NOT

* Do not return entities

---

## ❗ VALIDATION

### DO

* Use `@Valid` for request DTOs

---

## ⚠️ ERROR HANDLING

### DO

* Let exceptions propagate to global handler

### DO NOT

* Do not use try-catch in controller

---

## 🚫 DO NOT RULES

* No business logic
* No DB calls
* No entity exposure

---

## ⚙️ BEST PRACTICES

### DO

* Keep controllers thin
* Call only service layer
* Use meaningful method names:

  * createTask
  * getTasks

---

## 🧪 TDD RULES

### DO

* Write controller tests
* Mock service layer

---

## 🧠 AI ENFORCEMENT RULES

* MUST use DTOs
* MUST call service layer only
* MUST NOT include business logic
* MUST return proper HTTP responses

---

